WEBVTT

00:02.423 --> 00:03.754
Dre: The Johnson family
 loves Christmas.

00:03.754 --> 00:06.047
And for us, Christmas kicks off

00:06.047 --> 00:09.090
the moment Bow starts washing
 dishes after Thanksgiving.

00:09.090 --> 00:12.343
From that moment on,
 it's a countdown

00:12.343 --> 00:14.345
to our favorite holiday
 of the year

00:14.345 --> 00:18.229
when a joyous and inclusive
 spirit runs through the house.

00:18.229 --> 00:20.271
This year is extra special

00:20.271 --> 00:22.103
because of
 the pleasant surprise

00:22.103 --> 00:24.645
of my aged wife's fertility.

00:24.645 --> 00:26.197
And to top it off,

00:26.197 --> 00:29.320
my favorite
 person/international pop star

00:29.320 --> 00:31.031
was coming to stay with us

00:31.031 --> 00:33.614
with the baby she'd wished for
 for so long.

00:33.614 --> 00:37.288
And my least favorite person/
 international mooch

00:37.288 --> 00:39.620
was leaving,
 but not fast enough.

00:39.620 --> 00:42.253
Hey. That's my --
That's my --

00:42.253 --> 00:44.835
Okay.
All right.

00:44.835 --> 00:46.297
But there was
 something bittersweet

00:46.297 --> 00:48.008
about this holiday, too.

00:48.008 --> 00:51.051
My firstborn, Zoey,
 is a senior in high school,

00:51.051 --> 00:52.843
and she's about to leave
 the nest.

00:52.843 --> 00:54.515
Dad,
you're gazing at me again.

00:54.515 --> 00:56.637
Please don't go
to college!

01:00.271 --> 01:02.563
♪♪

01:02.563 --> 01:03.684
Hey,
what's happening, girl?

01:03.684 --> 01:05.275
I like your new room.

01:05.275 --> 01:07.108
Hey, what are you watching?
"TRL"?

01:07.108 --> 01:10.111
Dad, don't.
The friend thing -- it's weird.

01:10.111 --> 01:12.613
Yeah, I felt that.
Okay, look.

01:12.613 --> 01:15.656
This is your last Christmas
before you go to college,

01:15.656 --> 01:17.458
and I want to spend
some quality time with you.

01:17.458 --> 01:19.460
I was hoping we could make
some memories,

01:19.460 --> 01:21.081
do the greatest hits --

01:21.081 --> 01:25.045
perfect tree, cocoa,
matching PJs.

01:25.045 --> 01:26.257
We've never done
matching PJs.

01:26.257 --> 01:28.919
This is our last chance.

01:28.919 --> 01:30.261
It'll get weird soon.

01:30.261 --> 01:31.382
Hold on, Dad.

01:31.382 --> 01:34.014
If you wanted
to do Christmas stuff,

01:34.014 --> 01:35.516
just tell me that.

01:35.516 --> 01:37.888
I love Christmas.
Let's hang.

01:37.888 --> 01:39.600
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:42.933 --> 01:44.024
[ Voice breaking ]
We're gonna hang?

01:44.024 --> 01:46.106
Thank you.

01:46.106 --> 01:49.029
Should I look away while
you get yourself together?

01:49.029 --> 01:50.691
Yes, please!
Please look away!
 Okay, looking away.

01:50.691 --> 01:52.823
I don't want you
to remember me like this!

01:52.823 --> 01:54.235
Tell me when you're done.

01:54.235 --> 01:57.117
♪♪

01:57.117 --> 01:58.999
[ Sighs ]
Nope.
 Nope.

02:00.331 --> 02:01.582
Ooh,
I think this is for us.

02:01.582 --> 02:02.833
[ Gasps ]

02:02.833 --> 02:05.376
Ooh,
I bet it's a trampoline.

02:05.376 --> 02:07.958
Without looking at it,
it is not.

02:07.958 --> 02:09.840
-What are you two doing?
-Laundry.

02:09.840 --> 02:12.553
You don't need to lie to him.
He has no power.

02:12.553 --> 02:16.347
Well, a certain elf
watching from a distance does.

02:16.347 --> 02:19.099
And he will be very interested
in letting Santa know

02:19.099 --> 02:20.931
about these violations.

02:20.931 --> 02:22.683
Well, the elf
isn't in this room.

02:22.683 --> 02:25.606
So by his law,
none of this ever happened,

02:25.606 --> 02:28.979
so nobody saw nothing.

02:28.979 --> 02:30.401
You won't get away
with this.

02:30.401 --> 02:33.113
You think that magical
cross-legged sentry is a joke?

02:33.113 --> 02:35.486
I only see one joke
in here.

02:35.486 --> 02:37.738
It's me, isn't it?

02:37.738 --> 02:38.869
It's always you.

02:40.281 --> 02:42.783
[ Sighs ]

02:42.783 --> 02:44.245
Rainbow: Aww.
Aren't you the cutest?

02:44.245 --> 02:45.085
[ Laughs ]
 Oh, my goodness.

02:45.085 --> 02:46.166
[ Baby voice ]
You're so cute,

02:46.166 --> 02:47.708
I just want to put
your foot in my mouth.

02:47.708 --> 02:49.250
I'm gonna do it.
Ahhh!

02:49.250 --> 02:50.501
No, uh,
whoa, whoa, whoa.
 She's touching...

02:50.501 --> 02:52.343
C-Can -- Can you, um,
not put my baby's feet

02:52.343 --> 02:53.924
into the dirtiest part
of your body?

02:53.924 --> 02:54.925
[ Normal voice ]
Oh.

02:54.925 --> 02:55.966
Uh, maybe we just
play pretend,

02:55.966 --> 02:58.008
like air bites,
like, nyah-yah-yah.

02:58.008 --> 02:59.220
Nyah-yah-yah.
 Yeah.

02:59.220 --> 03:00.221
Okay.
 It's just as fun.

03:00.221 --> 03:01.602
Is it?
 Yeah!

03:01.602 --> 03:03.684
It's even more fun because
then my baby can still live.

03:03.684 --> 03:05.646
Oh!
Okay.

03:05.646 --> 03:07.608
Look at all the padding
around the baby's head.

03:07.608 --> 03:09.650
Looks like he's about to blast
off into outer space.

03:09.650 --> 03:11.902
We didn't even have
a car seat for Dre.
 What?

03:11.902 --> 03:14.615
He just rode shotgun and held
my cigarettes for me.
 [ Laughs ]

03:14.615 --> 03:16.737
I've got the burns
and the asthma to prove it.

03:16.737 --> 03:19.159
[ Laughs ] Ain't nobody wheeze
like my baby.

03:19.159 --> 03:20.581
[ Dre and Ruby laugh ]
 [ Beeping ]

03:20.581 --> 03:22.493
-What is that?
-Oh, it's a sleep monitor.

03:22.493 --> 03:24.415
It lets us know
if the baby isn't breathing

03:24.415 --> 03:26.627
or if his heart stops

03:26.627 --> 03:28.629
or if somebody tries
to snatch him.

03:28.629 --> 03:30.421
Ah.
 It's a little glitchy,
though,

03:30.421 --> 03:33.173
so seven, eight times a day,
we think our baby died.

03:33.173 --> 03:34.385
Other than that,
it's awesome.

03:34.385 --> 03:37.928
Wow. I forgot how silly
new parents are.

03:37.928 --> 03:40.471
[ Laughter ]
 Silly or not, this baby
has not cried once.

03:40.471 --> 03:42.303
Rainbow: Well, of course
you haven't cried.

03:42.303 --> 03:44.645
With all the beeping
and the blinking

03:44.645 --> 03:46.477
and the padding
and the heating,

03:46.477 --> 03:48.439
you don't have any time
for your own little thoughts,

03:48.439 --> 03:49.810
do you, sweetheart?

03:49.810 --> 03:52.313
Well, we need to tell
Auntie Bow Bow

03:52.313 --> 03:54.114
that Mommy has read
all the blogs

03:54.114 --> 03:56.156
and knows exactly
what babies need.

03:56.156 --> 03:59.530
Maybe Auntie Bow Bow is a little
out of touch touch.

03:59.530 --> 04:01.912
-Oh.
-Oh, come on, Ruby.

04:01.912 --> 04:02.953
Baby can't even talk,

04:02.953 --> 04:04.625
and they think
he can clearly track

04:04.625 --> 04:06.166
a passive-aggressive
conversation

04:06.166 --> 04:07.458
like a divorce arbitrator.

04:07.458 --> 04:08.539
You know, I miss Gene.

04:08.539 --> 04:10.040
Oh, yeah.
Gene was good.

04:10.040 --> 04:11.872
Dre:
All right, here we go.

04:11.872 --> 04:13.674
Heading to the garage

04:13.674 --> 04:15.426
to find our
Christmas ornaments.

04:15.426 --> 04:17.928
2016,
Zoey and Dre!

04:17.928 --> 04:19.048
Okay, I'm gonna switch
to slo-mo.

04:19.048 --> 04:20.010
All right.
Ugh!

04:20.010 --> 04:21.221
I can't switch
to slow-mo while I'm filming,

04:21.221 --> 04:22.303
so you're gonna
have to fake it.

04:22.303 --> 04:23.434
Okay? Go!

04:23.434 --> 04:27.648
[ Slo-mo ]
This is the best Christmas ever.

04:27.648 --> 04:29.019
[ Chuckles ]

04:29.019 --> 04:32.653
[ Slo-mo ]
You guys filming?

04:32.653 --> 04:34.605
Damn it, Junior!
Delete.

04:34.605 --> 04:37.698
I'm trying to spend
some time with my child.

04:37.698 --> 04:40.030
Okay, then.
I'll be fast.

04:40.030 --> 04:43.033
I'd like to bring up
the twins' behavior of late.

04:43.033 --> 04:44.955
They are making a mockery
of the elf!

04:44.955 --> 04:46.116
They're running amok!

04:46.116 --> 04:48.208
Do you even know
what they had for breakfast?

04:48.208 --> 04:49.620
Don't listen to him!

04:49.620 --> 04:52.252
We had a bowl of cereal
and fresh fruit.

04:52.252 --> 04:53.674
Uh, next to two slices
of toast,

04:53.674 --> 04:55.626
and a glass of OJ
to wash it all down.
 All down.

04:55.626 --> 04:56.877
Lies!

04:56.877 --> 04:58.128
They're just describing

04:58.128 --> 05:00.511
a balanced breakfast
they saw on television!

05:00.511 --> 05:02.633
You know what they really had?
 Junior.

05:02.633 --> 05:05.556
That cake you hid
in the vegetable crisper.

05:05.556 --> 05:06.887
Hold on.

05:06.887 --> 05:08.519
My shame cake?

05:08.519 --> 05:09.810
Torched it.
 Ah.

05:09.810 --> 05:11.692
[ Whimpers ]

05:11.692 --> 05:13.273
Get out of my sight.

05:13.273 --> 05:16.527
And if you even look
at my sadness cookies...

05:16.527 --> 05:19.780
You fix this, Junior.
You fix this now.

05:19.780 --> 05:21.362
I swear to God.

05:21.362 --> 05:23.944
You better not let them two
ruin Zoey's Christmas.

05:23.944 --> 05:25.285
You mean all
of our Christmases, ri--

05:25.285 --> 05:26.577
You heard what I said.

05:26.577 --> 05:28.619
♪♪

05:32.122 --> 05:33.874
How long do I need
to keep my finger here?

05:33.874 --> 05:35.165
What does it matter,
Earl?

05:35.165 --> 05:36.717
Your drinking hand's
still free.

05:36.717 --> 05:39.299
Yeah, well, when you're right,
you're right.

05:39.299 --> 05:41.051
♪ And the bells were ringing out
for Christmas Day ♪

05:41.051 --> 05:42.383
What the hell is this?

05:42.383 --> 05:44.134
Earl,
why is this happening?

05:44.134 --> 05:46.096
I don't know, but it's making me
want to beat somebody up.

05:46.096 --> 05:47.638
Knock, knock.

05:47.638 --> 05:49.139
Isn't this great?
Huh?

05:49.139 --> 05:51.392
I'm giving you guys
a sample of the CD I made

05:51.392 --> 05:53.353
so I could exchange gifts
without participating

05:53.353 --> 05:54.855
in the Christmas
industrial complex.

05:54.855 --> 05:56.356
Why are you connected
to my Sonos?

05:56.356 --> 05:58.108
Aren't you supposed
to be leaving?

05:58.108 --> 05:59.319
Yeah, yeah.
I'll give you a ride.

05:59.319 --> 06:00.901
Oh, no, no.
My flight's not until later.

06:00.901 --> 06:03.404
Here. Have a CD.
This is track four.

06:03.404 --> 06:05.656
It's an Irish dystopian vision
of Christmas in a drunk tank.

06:05.656 --> 06:08.118
You are also going to love
"Do They Know It's Christmas?"

06:08.118 --> 06:09.950
♪ The boys of the NYPD choir ♪
 Let me see that.

06:09.950 --> 06:12.703
♪ Were singing "Galway Bay" ♪
 Aah!

06:12.703 --> 06:15.876
♪ And the bells were ringing
out for Christmas Day ♪
 Now, I'm going to make
a real holiday playlist.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.127
[ Laughs ]

06:17.127 --> 06:18.919
I'm talking
about roasted chestnuts,

06:18.919 --> 06:21.712
angels singing,
little drummer boys.

06:21.712 --> 06:23.634
All of that
magnificent [bleep]

06:23.634 --> 06:24.885
♪♪

06:24.885 --> 06:26.176
Rainbow:
Hey, is everything okay?

06:26.176 --> 06:28.348
Yeah, I'm just preparing
his bath.

06:28.348 --> 06:30.310
I've got to hydrate
this bath flower

06:30.310 --> 06:31.642
and then I got to get
that music going

06:31.642 --> 06:33.183
and then I have his
massage oil that I'm preparing.

06:33.183 --> 06:34.314
Oh, my God.
Mm.

06:34.314 --> 06:36.146
And then I'm almost
ready to go.
 Okay.

06:36.146 --> 06:38.859
You know, Dre and I
used to just wash the babies

06:38.859 --> 06:40.481
in the kitchen sink.

06:40.481 --> 06:41.982
So the same kitchen sink
where you clean raw chicken.

06:41.982 --> 06:43.524
Yeah.
That's the one.

06:43.524 --> 06:44.825
That's interesting.
[ Laughs ]
 Uh-huh.

06:44.825 --> 06:46.617
You know, Gigi,

06:46.617 --> 06:48.579
germs are actually really good
for a baby's immune system.

06:48.579 --> 06:50.451
I know that 'cause I've had
four children,

06:50.451 --> 06:52.623
and I got another one
on the way.

06:52.623 --> 06:54.995
And I'm, uh --
I'm a doctor, so...

06:54.995 --> 06:56.206
[ Both laugh ]

06:56.206 --> 06:58.459
Yeah.
 Yeah, she likes to say that.

06:58.459 --> 07:01.041
Well, I'm -- I am,
and everybody seems to forget.

07:01.041 --> 07:02.673
[ Water splashing ]
 What are those?

07:02.673 --> 07:04.384
These are
temperature beads.

07:04.384 --> 07:06.256
And we just sit,
and we wait for 10 minutes

07:06.256 --> 07:07.347
until the smile appears.

07:07.347 --> 07:09.099
Okay.
[ Laughs ]
 What?

07:09.099 --> 07:11.431
Gigi,
you can use your elbow,

07:11.431 --> 07:13.393
and you just go like this.

07:13.393 --> 07:14.645
And ooh, whoop!

07:14.645 --> 07:16.817
Yep.
Bath is ready for the baby.

07:16.817 --> 07:18.108
Should I...?
 Yeah.

07:18.108 --> 07:19.820
See?

07:19.820 --> 07:21.692
It's delicate skin, so if it's
comfortable for your skin,

07:21.692 --> 07:23.023
then it's comfortable
for the baby.

07:23.023 --> 07:24.985
Yeah, I still want to wait for
the smiley face to come, though.

07:24.985 --> 07:26.276
Okay.
 I want to be safe.

07:26.276 --> 07:27.658
Yes, you, uh --
That makes sense.

07:27.658 --> 07:30.410
So you wait
for the beads to smile.

07:30.410 --> 07:32.332
I got another gadget
for you there, though.

07:32.332 --> 07:34.454
You just look right in here,
look in there,

07:34.454 --> 07:35.956
and you see
that you're doing too much.

07:35.956 --> 07:37.578
Touché, boo.

07:37.578 --> 07:38.839
[ Both chuckle ]

07:40.921 --> 07:42.292
Oh!
Found 'em!

07:42.292 --> 07:43.173
Oh!

07:43.173 --> 07:44.965
Sadness cookies.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.757
The man does know
his cookies.

07:46.757 --> 07:50.851
100% pure
uncut Double Stuf.

07:50.851 --> 07:52.052
Wow.

07:52.052 --> 07:53.263
Eating stolen cookies

07:53.263 --> 07:55.305
right in front of
Bear on the Chair.

07:55.305 --> 07:56.727
[ Dramatic chord plays ]

07:56.727 --> 07:59.269
What is that?
 Santa's eyes and ears.

07:59.269 --> 08:00.601
What happened to the elf?

08:00.601 --> 08:03.103
You've aged
out of his jurisdiction.

08:03.103 --> 08:05.025
You're on
Bear on the Chair's turf now.

08:05.025 --> 08:07.197
What are you
talking about?

08:07.197 --> 08:08.739
This isn't a thing.

08:08.739 --> 08:10.571
Zach Labich didn't believe,
either.

08:10.571 --> 08:12.873
10-year-old punk
did whatever he wanted.

08:12.873 --> 08:14.665
He crossed
Bear on the Chair,

08:14.665 --> 08:17.878
and let's just say
that was his last Christmas.

08:17.878 --> 08:19.790
He died?!
 He's dead to Santa.

08:19.790 --> 08:23.423
But go ahead.
Have another stolen Oreo.

08:23.423 --> 08:26.627
I'm not afraid
of that bear.

08:26.627 --> 08:28.048
Am I, Diane?

08:28.048 --> 08:31.632
Um...no.

08:31.632 --> 08:35.806
We are just going to put
these away because we are full.

08:35.806 --> 08:36.807
Hmm.

08:36.807 --> 08:39.019
We are just fine.

08:41.400 --> 08:43.943
I am so sorry we are
running out on you like this.

08:43.943 --> 08:45.566
Oh, no, it's fine.
Please, enjoy yourself.

08:45.566 --> 08:46.857
Get out of here.
Go.

08:46.857 --> 08:47.988
You know I got this.

08:47.988 --> 08:49.239
Where you guys going?

08:49.239 --> 08:50.240
Cher was
supposed to perform

08:50.240 --> 08:51.361
at this charity event,

08:51.361 --> 08:52.743
and she pulled out
at the last minute,

08:52.743 --> 08:54.154
and so they asked me
to fill in.

08:54.154 --> 08:55.786
Okay.
Who's going to watch the baby?

08:55.786 --> 08:57.658
I am.
 Oh.

08:57.658 --> 08:59.870
Are you sure about that, Bow?
'Cause, you know, my mom's here.

08:59.870 --> 09:02.002
Mama! Can you come down here
and help --
 Shh!

09:02.002 --> 09:03.543
Go.
Just go.

09:03.543 --> 09:04.965
And I've got this.
I've got it.

09:04.965 --> 09:06.166
You sure?
 Yeah.
 Yes.

09:06.166 --> 09:08.298
And if she doesn't,
my mom's here.

09:08.298 --> 09:09.720
Napoleon:
Well, look, if he gets fussy,

09:09.720 --> 09:11.592
just throw him in the mamaRoo
and he'll conk right out.

09:11.592 --> 09:13.303
And if that doesn't work,
you just play "Rump Shaker."

09:13.303 --> 09:14.595
I don't know why,
but it works.

09:14.595 --> 09:17.638
Guys, I have been a mom
for 16 years.

09:17.638 --> 09:18.809
I got this.

09:18.809 --> 09:20.310
And my mom's here.

09:20.310 --> 09:21.682
Thank you guys so much.

09:21.682 --> 09:22.683
I got it.
 Okay.

09:22.683 --> 09:24.524
Gigi: You be a good boy.
 [ Luca cries ]

09:26.566 --> 09:27.608
You got this, Bow?

09:27.608 --> 09:29.029
I got this.

09:29.029 --> 09:32.072
[ Crying continues ]

09:37.157 --> 09:38.659
So, Zoey and I spent
 the afternoon sorting through

09:38.659 --> 09:40.080
all the Christmas ornaments
 she'd made as a kid.

09:40.080 --> 09:41.291
Oh, this is my favorite one
right here.

09:41.291 --> 09:43.293
Santa's Little Zo-Zo.

09:43.293 --> 09:45.125
I just get cuter
with age, huh?

09:45.125 --> 09:46.877
I'm not even
being conceited.

09:46.877 --> 09:48.258
This is hard proof.

09:48.258 --> 09:49.549
Yeah, I can't believe

09:49.549 --> 09:51.381
your mother wanted me
to throw all this out.

09:51.381 --> 09:54.264
"Dre, it's a fire hazard.
Dre, it has lead in it.

09:54.264 --> 09:56.096
Dre, the babies
will choke on this."

09:56.096 --> 09:57.347
How do you even deal
with her?

09:57.347 --> 09:59.640
You know,
I'm barely hanging on.

09:59.640 --> 10:00.891
[ Sighs ]

10:00.891 --> 10:02.022
Oh, remember that?

10:02.022 --> 10:03.523
[ Laughs ] Yeah.

10:03.523 --> 10:05.145
[ Luca crying ]
 Okay.

10:05.145 --> 10:07.187
Hey!
The baby's crying!

10:07.187 --> 10:08.608
Is he, Junior?

10:08.608 --> 10:10.651
Why don't you use
the fancy egg-shell thing?

10:10.651 --> 10:13.613
Junior, I do not need gadgets
to put a baby down.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.656
I am a mother of four,

10:15.656 --> 10:18.328
and I have another one
on the way, okay?

10:18.328 --> 10:19.910
I'm a doctor, sweetheart.

10:19.910 --> 10:21.621
Okay.
 A doctor!

10:21.621 --> 10:24.004
Damn it.
I really need to lead with that.

10:24.004 --> 10:25.876
Okay, sweetheart.
I'm sorry.

10:25.876 --> 10:29.129
[ Nat King Cole's
"The Christmas Song" plays ]
 This.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.802
♪ Chestnuts roasting
on an open fire ♪
 This is Christmas music.

10:31.802 --> 10:35.465
The birth of our savior inspired
the people who wrote classics,

10:35.465 --> 10:38.098
like "White Christmas"
and "Silver Bells."

10:38.098 --> 10:39.099
They were Jewish.

10:39.099 --> 10:40.350
[ Sputters ]

10:40.350 --> 10:41.641
Well, all of these songs

10:41.641 --> 10:42.973
were written
by Jewish composers.

10:42.973 --> 10:44.104
Very musical people.

10:44.104 --> 10:45.896
Also know how
to finely slice a meat.

10:45.896 --> 10:48.068
Even Nat King Cole's song?

10:48.068 --> 10:49.940
Especially
Nat King Cole's song.

10:49.940 --> 10:51.271
You know what?
 [ Glass thuds ]

10:51.271 --> 10:52.733
I'm gonna make
my own Christmas playlist

10:52.733 --> 10:54.234
that'll blow
both of yours out the water.

10:54.234 --> 10:56.576
Mm.
You do that, Earl.

10:56.576 --> 10:59.780
♪ Everybody knows ♪
 So...it's just us.

10:59.780 --> 11:01.782
♪ A turkey and some mistletoe ♪
 And it appears we're...

11:01.782 --> 11:03.083
under the mistletoe.

11:03.083 --> 11:04.955
Uh,
I have a cold sore.

11:04.955 --> 11:06.336
♪ Helps to make... ♪
 So do I, darling.

11:06.336 --> 11:07.998
So do I.

11:07.998 --> 11:09.499
♪♪

11:09.499 --> 11:10.340
Ooh.

11:11.551 --> 11:12.552
Oh!

11:12.552 --> 11:13.844
[ Laughs ]

11:13.844 --> 11:15.425
I got you
in my cross hairs!

11:15.425 --> 11:17.968
Die!
Die, you dirty --

11:17.968 --> 11:18.799
[ Dramatic chord plays ]

11:18.799 --> 11:22.182
Um, I mean, pass away

11:22.182 --> 11:25.015
after a long,
fulfilling life

11:25.015 --> 11:28.899
in your sleep
on your own terms.

11:28.899 --> 11:30.901
Yeah.
 Do you think he bought it?

11:30.901 --> 11:32.612
Just turn and walk away.

11:34.614 --> 11:37.317
♪♪

11:37.317 --> 11:39.870
Junior:
It's almost too easy.

11:41.872 --> 11:43.703
[ Grunts ]

11:43.703 --> 11:45.665
Damn.

11:45.665 --> 11:49.589
♪ And this Christmas will be ♪
 [ Laughs ] Yeah.

11:49.589 --> 11:52.422
♪ A very special Christmas ♪
 Soul Glo needs to put that
 on his playlist.

11:52.422 --> 11:53.543
Mm-hmm.

11:53.543 --> 11:55.335
I grew up
on songs like this.
 Mm-hmm.

11:55.335 --> 11:57.217
Like, uh, "Every Day
Will be like a Holiday"

11:57.217 --> 12:00.470
or, uh, uh, "All I Want
for Christmas is You."

12:00.470 --> 12:01.762
[ Laughs ]

12:01.762 --> 12:04.724
You did not grow up
on a Mariah Carey song

12:04.724 --> 12:06.897
from 1994.
 Shut up, boy.

12:06.897 --> 12:08.188
You don't know what the hell
you talking about.

12:08.188 --> 12:09.149
That song came out
in the '50s.

12:09.149 --> 12:10.690
He's right!

12:10.690 --> 12:13.273
Earl and I first made love
to that song in 1971.

12:13.273 --> 12:14.274
Didn't we, baby?
Remember?

12:14.274 --> 12:15.275
Sure did.
 Hey!

12:15.275 --> 12:17.447
You two are crazy.

12:17.447 --> 12:20.911
Mariah Carey wrote
that song in 1994.

12:20.911 --> 12:22.282
Well, then,
you're telling me

12:22.282 --> 12:25.125
that five-octave superstar
Mariah Carey

12:25.125 --> 12:26.706
is a time traveler.

12:26.706 --> 12:28.538
'Cause I heard that song
when I was a child.

12:28.538 --> 12:29.830
Trust me.

12:29.830 --> 12:31.541
If she was a time traveler,

12:31.541 --> 12:33.333
she'd go back in time

12:33.333 --> 12:35.585
and tighten up that prenup
with Nick Cannon.

12:35.585 --> 12:37.467
[ Crying ]

12:37.467 --> 12:38.839
Okay, come on.

12:38.839 --> 12:41.471
You're -- You're in your egg.
You had a bottle.

12:41.471 --> 12:43.013
I-I put you in the bath.

12:43.013 --> 12:46.056
I even waited
until the pearls smiled.

12:46.056 --> 12:48.308
Okay, are you seriously
gonna make me do this?

12:48.308 --> 12:52.522
Okay, okay. Okay, okay.
I'll try anything.

12:52.522 --> 12:54.774
♪ All I wanna do is
 zoom-a-zoom-zoom-zoom ♪

12:54.774 --> 12:57.277
♪ And a poom-poom,
 just shake ya rump ♪
 [ Crying stops ]

12:57.277 --> 12:59.900
♪ All I wanna do is
 zoom-a-zoom-zoom-zoom ♪
 Seriously?
"Rump Shaker"?

12:59.900 --> 13:01.822
♪ And a poom-poom,
 just shake ya rump ♪
 Are you kidding me?

13:01.822 --> 13:02.903
♪ All I wanna do is
 zoom-a-zoom-zoom-- ♪

13:02.903 --> 13:04.074
[ Music stops ]

13:04.074 --> 13:05.745
[ Crying resumes ]

13:05.745 --> 13:07.667
Okay, okay. I'll put it back on.
I'll put it back on.

13:07.667 --> 13:09.789
♪ All I wanna do is
 zoom-a-zoom-zoom-zoom ♪
 It's coming back.
Here it is.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.671
[ Music stops, cellphone rings ]
 Oh, my God.

13:11.671 --> 13:12.873
[ Crying resumes ]
 Oh, God. Okay.

13:12.873 --> 13:14.334
Okay.
Hold on.

13:14.334 --> 13:15.876
Hi.
Gigi.

13:15.876 --> 13:17.087
How's it going?

13:17.087 --> 13:18.919
Oh, great!
Can you believe it?

13:18.919 --> 13:20.680
Luca actually
fell asleep in my arms.

13:20.680 --> 13:22.092
Sounds like he's crying.
 Nope, nope.

13:22.092 --> 13:24.925
Uh, it's just, uh,
um, a documentary

13:24.925 --> 13:27.307
that I-I'm watching
about helicopter parenting

13:27.307 --> 13:29.519
and how the the kids
get so sad

13:29.519 --> 13:31.231
that the parents
are always calling

13:31.231 --> 13:32.392
and checking up on them.

13:32.392 --> 13:33.733
Is everything okay?
 Yeah, yeah, yeah!

13:33.733 --> 13:35.735
Everything
is totally fine.

13:35.735 --> 13:36.937
Everything is fine.

13:36.937 --> 13:38.939
He doesn't even know
you're gone.

13:38.939 --> 13:40.110
Okay.
Can I at least say goo--

13:40.110 --> 13:42.032
I'll tell him for you!
Okay. Bye, girl!

13:42.032 --> 13:44.494
[ Sighs ]

13:44.494 --> 13:47.037
[ Crying continues ]

13:47.037 --> 13:48.869
You're a monster.

13:48.869 --> 13:50.660
No. No, I-I-I...

13:50.660 --> 13:53.663
♪♪

13:53.663 --> 13:55.455
Zoey: Wow.

13:55.455 --> 13:56.796
I think we put up

13:56.796 --> 13:59.509
every single one of my ornaments
since kindergarten.

13:59.509 --> 14:00.720
Mm-hmm.

14:00.720 --> 14:02.592
So, should we light
this baby up?

14:02.592 --> 14:03.924
Let's do it.
[ Claps hands ]

14:03.924 --> 14:05.845
Hey, everybody! Come down!
We're about to light the tree!

14:05.845 --> 14:07.637
You extinguished
that tree's light

14:07.637 --> 14:09.099
the moment you cut it down.

14:09.099 --> 14:10.600
And why
are you still here?

14:10.600 --> 14:12.852
Hm.

14:12.852 --> 14:15.025
[ Gasps ]
My favorite.

14:15.025 --> 14:17.938
Mm!
I mean, why do I need a will?

14:17.938 --> 14:19.609
All I ask
is that you're fair

14:19.609 --> 14:21.611
and give your siblings
whatever it is you don't want.

14:21.611 --> 14:22.862
Okay?

14:22.862 --> 14:24.945
Oh, got to go.
Got to go.

14:24.945 --> 14:26.536
[ Dramatic chord plays ]

14:26.536 --> 14:27.657
You guys ready
to see this?

14:27.657 --> 14:29.449
[ "Rump Shaker" plays
on headphones ]

14:29.449 --> 14:30.951
Oh, my God.
Really?

14:30.951 --> 14:33.543
He is listening
to a TED Talk,

14:33.543 --> 14:34.544
not "Rump Shaker."

14:34.544 --> 14:36.046
Are you good at anything?

14:36.046 --> 14:37.667
Dre: All right,
get your cameras ready

14:37.667 --> 14:40.000
for Zoey and Dre's --
and no one else's --

14:40.000 --> 14:42.382
Perfect Christmas 2016.

14:42.382 --> 14:43.093
Hurtful.

14:45.265 --> 14:48.428
[ Cheers and applause ]

14:48.428 --> 14:50.270
[ Electricity crackles ]

14:50.270 --> 14:51.011
-What the...
-What is that?

14:51.011 --> 14:54.014
[ All screaming ]

14:58.568 --> 14:59.649
My baby!

14:59.649 --> 15:01.861
So, so hurtful!

15:01.861 --> 15:03.113
[ Smoke detector beeping ]

15:07.988 --> 15:10.450
Whoo!
That's the last of it.

15:10.450 --> 15:11.871
I saved the house!

15:11.871 --> 15:14.124
Damn it, Junior!
You got it on the chair!

15:14.124 --> 15:15.335
That was the first chair
that I bought!

15:15.335 --> 15:16.957
The best chair ever!

15:16.957 --> 15:19.839
Your grandmother held you for
the first time in that chair!

15:19.839 --> 15:21.461
You owe your grandmother
an apology!

15:21.461 --> 15:22.963
And damn it,
you owe us all an apology!

15:22.963 --> 15:25.465
Oh, please, Dre.
  You did it.

15:25.465 --> 15:27.847
After years of trying, you
finally burned the house down!

15:27.847 --> 15:29.309
Ruby:
What were you thinking?

15:29.309 --> 15:31.011
Popsicle sticks,
tissue paper --

15:31.011 --> 15:32.812
it's just a pile
of kindling.

15:32.812 --> 15:33.853
And any idiot knows

15:33.853 --> 15:35.725
you're supposed to check
the lights first!

15:35.725 --> 15:37.437
Johan: No, this issue
wasn't electric.

15:37.437 --> 15:38.938
That tree was bone dry --

15:38.938 --> 15:40.940
a reminder that
we cannot tame nature.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.443
Shut up, Johan!
It wasn't that big of a deal!

15:43.443 --> 15:44.864
Seems like
a pretty big deal.

15:44.864 --> 15:46.826
T-T-To be honest,
we're lucky.

15:46.826 --> 15:48.278
No one was injured.

15:48.278 --> 15:51.201
Except the chair
that Junior ruined.

15:51.201 --> 15:53.623
Boo, Junior!
Boo, Junior!

15:53.623 --> 15:55.125
Come on, everybody!
Boo!

15:55.125 --> 15:57.207
No, Dad!
Not this time!

15:58.498 --> 16:00.840
You ruined Christmas.

16:00.840 --> 16:01.791
What?

16:01.791 --> 16:03.173
[ Laughs ]

16:03.173 --> 16:05.045
Rainbow: That's my...
 Yeah, you tell him, boy.

16:05.045 --> 16:06.346
Mother Nature wins
again.
 [ Sighs ]

16:06.346 --> 16:07.887
You broke my heart.

16:07.887 --> 16:09.429
Unbelievable.

16:09.429 --> 16:11.721
It's a waste
of a perfectly good tree, son.

16:11.721 --> 16:14.554
It's gonna take a while
to come back from this one.

16:14.554 --> 16:16.556
[ Sighs ] My God.

16:16.556 --> 16:18.308
♪♪

16:29.029 --> 16:30.780
Hi, backup shame cake.

16:32.992 --> 16:35.325
You don't think
I ruined Christmas, do you?

16:35.325 --> 16:36.826
[ High-pitched ] No, Dre.

16:36.826 --> 16:38.708
I don't think
you ruined Christmas at all.

16:38.708 --> 16:40.120
I love you.

16:40.120 --> 16:43.123
[ Normal voice ]
I love you, too.

16:43.123 --> 16:44.964
You're my family now.

16:47.177 --> 16:49.629
Do you need a minute
to pull yourself together?

16:49.629 --> 16:50.930
No.

16:50.930 --> 16:53.973
[ Voice breaking ]
This is who I am.

16:53.973 --> 16:57.637
I'm sorry I let you take
the fall back there.

16:57.637 --> 17:00.850
[ Normal voice ]
I deserved it.

17:00.850 --> 17:02.021
I'm stupid.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.733
I got too caught up

17:03.733 --> 17:06.445
in wanting to have one
last perfect Christmas.

17:06.445 --> 17:08.568
But instead,

17:08.568 --> 17:10.069
I burned up
all our memories.

17:10.069 --> 17:13.282
Are you kidding me, Dad?
Those weren't all our memories.

17:13.282 --> 17:15.204
Besides, this will be

17:15.204 --> 17:18.208
the most memorable Christmas
we'll ever have.

17:18.208 --> 17:19.868
You almost killed us.

17:19.868 --> 17:22.712
I did, didn't I?

17:22.712 --> 17:25.875
And this isn't gonna be
our last Christmas together.

17:25.875 --> 17:28.218
Next year will be
the baby's first Christmas.

17:28.218 --> 17:29.969
Do you think I'd miss that?

17:29.969 --> 17:32.512
Come on.

17:32.512 --> 17:33.883
Ohhhh.

17:33.883 --> 17:35.135
I'm here, too, Dad.

17:40.019 --> 17:40.940
Bring it in, son.

17:40.940 --> 17:42.312
Bring it on in.

17:42.312 --> 17:43.893
Aw, I love you guys.

17:43.893 --> 17:44.684
Love you, too.

17:44.684 --> 17:46.146
Mm.

17:46.146 --> 17:48.778
I'm so sorry
I had to call you.

17:48.778 --> 17:51.030
Bow, your house was on fire
with my baby inside of it.

17:51.030 --> 17:53.533
I think you may have
legally had to call me.

17:53.533 --> 17:56.075
I know, but [sighs] the charity
event and all the kids.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.288
Oh, Bow, stop, stop.

17:58.288 --> 17:59.499
I didn't go.

17:59.499 --> 18:01.751
What? What do you mean?
Did it get canceled?

18:01.751 --> 18:04.704
Bow, Kids Town Help USA
is not a real charity.

18:04.704 --> 18:06.626
Me and Napoleon got

18:06.626 --> 18:09.549
the most expensive hotel room
that we could find,

18:09.549 --> 18:10.920
and we took a nap.

18:10.920 --> 18:12.842
So you made up
a charity event

18:12.842 --> 18:14.344
so that you could
take a nap?

18:14.344 --> 18:17.847
No, I made up a charity

18:17.847 --> 18:20.930
because I am struggling
being a mom.

18:20.930 --> 18:22.602
What are you talking about?

18:22.602 --> 18:24.644
Gigi, come on.
You're killing it.

18:24.644 --> 18:26.025
I mean,
you have everything.

18:26.025 --> 18:27.397
You got the mamaRoo

18:27.397 --> 18:30.230
and the -- the bath pearls
that smile and --

18:30.230 --> 18:31.441
I have everything

18:31.441 --> 18:34.404
because I am hoping
that I will buy something

18:34.404 --> 18:37.537
that makes me feel like
I know what the heck I'm doing.

18:37.537 --> 18:40.540
Sweetheart, why didn't you
just ask if you needed help?

18:40.540 --> 18:43.373
Because when you try
this hard to have a baby,

18:43.373 --> 18:45.795
you feel like
you have no right to complain.

18:45.795 --> 18:49.749
Mm.
 Especially
to "the" Rainbow Johnson.

18:49.749 --> 18:52.051
Uh, are you talking
about this Rainbow Johnson?

18:52.051 --> 18:53.383
Oh, yeah.

18:53.383 --> 18:55.305
Because Gigi, Luca cried

18:55.305 --> 18:57.347
the entire time
that you were gone.

18:57.347 --> 18:58.678
Oh, no.
 Yes.

18:58.678 --> 19:00.220
I was actually
a little bit relieved

19:00.220 --> 19:01.351
that the house
caught fire.

19:01.351 --> 19:02.182
Just saying.

19:02.182 --> 19:03.473
[ Chuckles ]
 Yeah, okay.

19:03.473 --> 19:05.144
I'm scared.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.526
I'm scared.

19:06.526 --> 19:09.269
It's been 10 years since
I've had a baby in this house.

19:09.269 --> 19:10.530
And I don't know
what I'm doing.

19:10.530 --> 19:11.981
You have four
amazing kids.

19:11.981 --> 19:13.273
They're fine.

19:13.273 --> 19:15.735
Okay, so,
if you don't have this down,

19:15.735 --> 19:17.657
what the hell
am I supposed to do?

19:17.657 --> 19:18.828
You're the perfect mom.

19:18.828 --> 19:20.660
I hate that expression
so much.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.702
What, everybody else
gets to have flaws,

19:22.702 --> 19:23.993
and moms
have to be perfect?

19:23.993 --> 19:25.124
[ Chuckles ]

19:25.124 --> 19:26.456
Oh, God.

19:26.456 --> 19:29.088
It's been so long.
My God.

19:29.088 --> 19:31.211
And I'm older,
and kids are...

19:31.211 --> 19:34.344
Babies.
Babies are stronger now.

19:34.344 --> 19:35.385
Like weed.

19:36.966 --> 19:38.218
I'm really sorry
I was so judgy.

19:38.218 --> 19:39.219
Yeah.

19:39.219 --> 19:40.640
Here is the deal.

19:40.640 --> 19:42.101
Okay.

19:42.101 --> 19:43.393
From now on,

19:43.393 --> 19:45.144
we are gonna
support each other.

19:45.144 --> 19:46.145
I like that.

19:46.145 --> 19:48.398
Because we are amazing.
 Mm!

19:48.398 --> 19:51.441
We should all support
each other, but we can't.

19:51.441 --> 19:53.983
[ Chuckles ]
'Cause you two are failures.

19:53.983 --> 19:55.575
[ "This Christmas" plays ]
 [ Laughs ]
Come on with Grandma.

19:57.026 --> 20:01.200
Every day, Gigi.
Every day.

20:01.200 --> 20:03.413
♪ Hang all the mistletoe ♪

20:03.413 --> 20:05.785
Things are rarely perfect.

20:05.785 --> 20:07.917
Whether you're trying
 to find the perfect song...

20:07.917 --> 20:10.129
♪ This Christmas ♪

20:10.129 --> 20:13.293
♪ The fireside
is blazing bright ♪

20:13.293 --> 20:14.964
...worrying about
 the perfect behavior...

20:14.964 --> 20:19.098
♪ We're caroling
through the night ♪

20:19.098 --> 20:20.300
...missing the perfect flight.

20:20.300 --> 20:23.643
♪ And this Christmas will be ♪

20:23.643 --> 20:27.477
And sometimes, you get scared
 you're not the perfect parent.

20:27.477 --> 20:31.481
Point is, you hardly remember
 the perfect things.

20:31.481 --> 20:33.653
♪♪

20:33.653 --> 20:36.195
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
  But when perfect goes wrong,

20:36.195 --> 20:38.658
those are the memories
 that last forever.

20:38.658 --> 20:41.070
♪ All over the land ♪

20:45.415 --> 20:48.037
[ Sighs ] Dre.
This has got to stop.

20:48.037 --> 20:51.170
This is
my insomnia cupcake.

20:52.422 --> 20:53.793
Really, Dre?

20:53.793 --> 20:55.465
Those are
my sleepy-time Cheetos

20:55.465 --> 20:57.757
because the sugar in my cupcake
keeps me up at night.

20:57.757 --> 20:59.679
That's disgusting. What else do
you have hidden here, huh?

20:59.679 --> 21:00.720
Nothing.
 What else?

21:00.720 --> 21:02.882
Uh, that's soap.
And that's floss.

21:07.096 --> 21:08.558
Okay. Okay.

21:08.558 --> 21:11.020
Those are my marshmallows
for my morning time s'mores.

21:11.020 --> 21:12.271
And that is it.

21:12.271 --> 21:13.733
Aw, man,
you have a problem, dude.

21:13.733 --> 21:15.274
I do not have a problem.
 Yes, you do.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.527
I do not have a problem.

21:21.401 --> 21:22.822
[ Whispers ]
She will never find you.
